// COMPLETION
// ──────────────────────────────────────────

scene "completion" {
    index: "a33";
    format: "markdown";
    concept: "mastery_check";
    title: "🎉 Lesson Complete!";
    body: """
## Congratulations!

You have completed the **Complete Trigonometric Ratios Masterclass** covering all **48 formulas**.

### What You Mastered

✅ 6 Basic Ratios (SOH-CAH-TOA)
✅ 3 Reciprocal Identities
✅ 3 Pythagorean Identities
✅ 2 Quotient Identities
✅ 6 Co-function Identities
✅ 3 Even-Odd Identities
✅ 6 Sum & Difference Formulas
✅ 3 Double Angle Formulas
✅ 3 Half Angle Formulas
✅ 4 Product-to-Sum Formulas
✅ 4 Sum-to-Product Formulas
✅ 3 Triple Angle Formulas
✅ Law of Sines & Law of Cosines
✅ 10 MCQ Speed Tricks

### Next Steps
1. **Review the Cheat Sheet** (Scene a31) until you can recall all 48 formulas from memory
2. **Practice with timed MCQs** — aim for under 30 seconds per question
3. **Revisit any module** where you were looped back for review
4. **Focus on pattern recognition** — the fastest solvers don't calculate, they recognize

### The Golden Rule

> *"Don't memorize 48 separate formulas. Learn the 6 basic ratios, the unit circle, and the sum formulas. Everything else is derivation."*

If you understand **why** each formula works (from the unit circle and angle addition), you can reconstruct any formula in seconds — even under exam pressure.

---

**You are now equipped to solve any trigonometric ratios problem.** 🚀
""";
}